dical research, lead optimization and translational services, and bioanalytical testing services. This segment also provides clinical pharmacology services, including first-in-human trials and early patient proof of concept studies of new pharmaceuticals at its clinics in the United States and the United Kingdom. The Late-Stage Development segment offers central laboratory services to biotechnology and pharmaceutical customers; and clinical development services, such as the full management of Phase II through IV clinical studies, study design and modeling, co-ordination of study activities, trial logistics, monitoring of study site performance, clinical data management and biostatistical analysis, and medical writing and regulatory services, as well as periapproval services. This segment also provides market access services, including reimbursement and healthcare economics consulting services, which comprise outcomes and pharmacoeconomic studies, reimbursement planning, reimbursement advocacy programs, risk evaluation and mitigation strategy services, registry services, specialty pharmacy services, and managed market contracting services; and clinical trial support services, such as interactive voice and Web response, and cardiac safety services. The company also provides laboratory testing services to the chemical, agrochemical, and food industries. Covance Inc. was founded in 1987 and is headquartered in Princeton, New Jersey. As of February 19, 2015, Covance Inc. operates as a subsidiary of Laboratory Corp. of America Holdings.','8000.80','6150.70','5369.90','na','3040.20','51.90','1018.20','Customer relationships','Customer Relationships','1830.30','28.00','Trade names and trademarks','Trade Names','270.50','15.00','Technology','Developed Technology','74.50','10.00','Favorable leases','Others','5.50','8.00','0','0','0','0','0','0','0','0','','','','https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/920148/000092014816000162/lh10-k2015.htm','B8MeLa-Co8411','Final'),(337,'PAREXEL International Corporation','PRXL','Quantum Solutions India','04/13/15','Healthcare','Medical Research Equipment, Other','Business Combination','Quantum Solutions India operates as a contract research organization that specializes in providing drug safety services for pharmaceutical industry worldwide. It offers pharmacovigilance services, including single case processing that include processing of individual case safety reports (ICSR) originating from various sources; analysis of grouped/aggregate data reports; and safety database hosting with electronic regulatory reporting. The company also provides medical writing programs, including safety narratives (CSR, DSMBs etc.); risk management plans (RMPs) and RMP updates; clinical study protocols and protocols; clinical summaries/product feasibility reports for medical devices; patient diary cards (PDC), informed consent form (ICF), subject information sheet (SIS), case report forms (CRFs); and guided questionnaires. In addition, it offers literature search review services that include literature search (Embase, PubMed, DataStar, QUOSA, Infotrieve); review of abstracts for inclusion in ICSRs, periodic safety update reports (PSURs) and other specialized reports; request for articles through libraries and portals; review of articles for inclusion in ICSRs, PSURs, and other specialized reports; review of non-indexed journals; translations. The company provides services in various therapeutic areas that include oncology, infections and infestations, dermatology, cardiovascular, ophthalmology, rheumatology, immunology/autoimmune diseases, metabolic disorders, hematology, urology, nephrology, virology, psychiatric and CNS disorders, medical devices, and pain. Quantum Solutions India was founded in 2004 and is based in Chandigarh, India. As of April 13, 2015, Quantum Solutions India operates as a subsidiary of PAREXEL International Corporation.','94.68','93.58','93.58','na','24.06','na','1.96','Customer relationships','C