ally motivated threats; Critical Infrastructure, which focuses on cyber threats against corporate and national infrastructure; Enterprise that focuses on the threat, geopolitical, and legal trends affecting the business enterprise, including cloud, mobile, and smart devices; and Vulnerability and Exploitation, which tracks vulnerabilities from discovery to patching, exploit development, regional propagation of exploit code, and ongoing malicious campaigns observed in the wild. The company also provides ThreatService, a cyber intelligence service that enables an organization to begin to connect security investments and operations to the business, such as Threat Diagnostics to identify an organization’s threat profile and highlighting the threat sources targeting their assets and associated tactical and strategic implications; Breach Diagnostics that identify the scope of an incident, as well as enables the enterprise to quickly respond to an incident with an intelligence-led approach; and intelligence integration services. In addition, it offers ThreatScape API that enables organizations to integrate the cyber threat intelligence with their security technologies and processes. The company was founded in 2006 and is based in Dallas, Texas. It has threat analysis centers in the United States, the Netherlands, India, and Australia. As of January 14, 2016, iSight Security, Inc. operates as a subsidiary of FireEye, Inc.','na','261.8','na','39.1','206.6','na','na','Customer relationships','Customer Relationships','33.7','7.0','Content','Developed Technology','30.1','4.0','developed technology','Developed Technology','17.1','5.0','Trade name','Trade Names','3.1','5.0','Non-compete agreements','Non-Compete Agreements','1.1','2.0','0','0','0','0','','','','https://www.sec.gov/cgi-bin/viewer?action=view&cik=1370880&accession_number=0001370880-17-000008&xbrl_type=v#','B8SoFi-iS8477','Final 08-04'),(476,'Fiserv, Inc.','FISV','ACI Worldwide, Inc., Community Financial Services Bus