igners through a combination of manufacturers’ representatives, distributors, and direct sales people in the United States, the Asia Pacific, Europe, and internationally. The company was founded in 1983 and is headquartered in Beaverton, Oregon. As of June 24, 2016, Cascade Microtech Inc. operates as a subsidiary of FormFactor Inc.','440.9','365.8','325.1','0','158.1','38.3','19.9','Developed technology','Developed Technology','91.1','4.7','Customer relationships','Customer Relationships','23.1','6.8','Order backlog','Backlog','15.6','0.5','Trade name','Trade Names','7.6','3.5','In-process research and development','In-Process R&D','12.4','Indefinite','0','0','0','0','','','','https://www.sec.gov/cgi-bin/viewer?action=view&cik=1039399&accession_number=0001039399-17-000009&xbrl_type=v#','B8SeFo-Ca8509','Final 10-11'),(480,'Fortinet, Inc.','FTNT','AccelOps, Inc.','06/07/2016','Information Technology','Software','Business Combination','AccelOps, Inc. provides software to monitor performance and security of information technology infrastructure and applications. The company offers products and solutions in the areas of cloud security, performance and availability monitoring, big data analytics, managed service providers, asset discovery and change management, security monitoring, cloud and virtualization monitoring, and IT operations management. It serves technology; healthcare; education; manufacturing; energy, utilities, and transportation; retail, wholesale, and distributors; financial services and insurance; sports, entertainment, and hospitality; government; and telecommunications industries in the United States and internationally. AccelOps, Inc. was formerly known as ProspectHills, Inc. and changed its name to AccelOps, Inc. in June 2009. The company was founded in 2007 and is headquartered in Santa Clara, California. As of June 7, 2016, AccelOps, Inc. operates as a subsidiary of Fortinet, Inc.','31.7','22.3','22.1','0','9.9','na','0.2','Developed technology','De