nt and detect threats; Encrypted Traffic Management solution, which enables organizations to meet business needs of maintaining privacy and compliance; and Incident Response, Analytics, and Forensics solution that allows organizations to capture all traffic that passes through the network, inspect that traffic for malicious content or activity, identify the cause and impact of threats, and feed key findings back into the security infrastructure. In addition, it offers Web Application Firewall, a product that protects against threats; Reverse Proxy, a proxy for critical applications and networks to the Internet; and a portfolio of network performance products to assist with application performance visibility, network usage management, network optimization, bandwidth allocation control, and network caching. The company primarily markets and sells its solutions through a two-tiered channel of solution providers, systems integrators, value-added resellers, and distributors to oil, gas, energy, and automotive companies, as well as banks. Blue Coat, Inc. was founded in 2014 and is headquartered in Sunnyvale, California. As of August 1, 2016, Blue Coat, Inc. operates as a subsidiary of Symantec Corporation.','6093.0','4819.0','4673.0','0','4086.0','na','54.0','Customer relationships','Customer Relationships','844.0','7.0','Developed technology and patents','Developed Technology','739.0','4.3','trade names','Trade Names','4.0','2.0','Product backlog','Backlog','2.0','0.3','0','0','0','0','0','0','0','0','','','','https://www.sec.gov/cgi-bin/viewer?action=view&cik=849399&accession_number=0000849399-17-000006&xbrl_type=v#','B8SoSy-Bl8517','Preliminary'),(567,'Synchronoss Technologies, Inc.','SNCR','Openwave Messaging, Inc.','03/01/2016','Information Technology','Software','Business Combination','Openwave Messaging, Inc. provides messaging solutions for customers in the United States and internationally. Its products include Email Mx, a carrier-grade white-label multi-channel 